            . I am a <rs id="t18200918-203-viclabel1174" type="occupation">merchant</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18200918-203-victim2014 t18200918-203-viclabel1174"></join>, and live in the Adelphi. On the 9th of July, about ten o'clock at night, I was coming along the <placeName id="t18200918-203-crimeloc1175">Strand</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18200918-203-crimeloc1175" type="placeName" value="Strand"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18200918-203-crimeloc1175" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18200918-203-off1172 t18200918-203-crimeloc1175"></join>, felt something touch my pocket, looked round, and caught hold of the prisoner, who was immediately behind me, and took a handkerchief from his waistcoat, which was not mine. A person came up, and said, in his hearing, that he saw the prisoner give my handkerchief to another. I gave him in charge.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18200918-203-person2016">
                  THOMAS 
                  GROVES
               <interp inst="t18200918-203-person2016" type="surname" value="GROVES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200918-203-person2016" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18200918-203-person2016" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a sword-cutler. I was going down the Strand, and saw the prisoner in company with another. I saw the prisoner take the handkerchief from the prosecutor's coat-pocket, and give it to one of the others, who ran across the street. The prosecutor turned round, and I secured him. I saw it distinctly.</p>
